narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend it for another student.

As a whole, Math 112 is exactly what you'd expect of it: If you have some background with calculus, then it shouldn't be too difficult at all. However, for those with absolutely no background whatsoever, be prepared to put in a lot of work. That being said, between your professors, TA's, and peer tutors, there are several resources available o you to help along the way.

Math 112 is a well organized class, in which you cover a lot of material and it is important to have background knowledge before going into it. It is fast paced and not easy. I would recommend this for someone who has already taken some form of calculus.
MATH 112 covers Calculus 1. It is a good course to take if you are looking to fulfill your QR requirement and is a class I would recommend.
